Paramedics had declared her dead at the scene of a deadly road collision in the early hours of 24 June. CAPE TOWN - The Gauteng Health Department is investigating after a woman was found alive in a mortuary fridge in Carletonville, west of Johannesburg. Paramedics had declared her dead at the scene of a deadly road collision in the early hours of 24 June. A morgue official then discovered she was alive several hours after the crash. She was then rushed to the hospital. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)